The paper deals with the problem of sorting under non-uniform comparison costs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a randomized algorithm, which involves analyzing the probability of certain events, making it relevant to the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of graphs and forbidden edges in the problem formulation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithmic approach to the problem, which involves analyzing the structure of the input graph, making it relevant to the category of graph theory (cs.GT).
